<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-460-386  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 460 386.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  May 3 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>US Sprint unveils medical imaging breakthrough.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Blankenhorn, Dana.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   US Sprint Communications Co. (innovations).andO;Product:   Apple Macintosh (Microcomputer) (usage).andO;Topic:     TelecommunicationsMedical IssuesImaging TechnologyImage Processing.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>US SPRINT UNVEILS MEDICAL IMAGING BREAKTHROUGH KANSAS CITY, MISSOURI, U.S.A.,andO;1990 APR 30 (NB) -- US Sprint will demonstrate medical imaging over phonelines at the Fifth Annual Conference on Information Technology in the HealthSciences in Memphis, TN.andP;  Using its Virtual Private Network (VPN) 56 service,US Sprint and James Lear, M.D., chief of nuclear medicine and associateprofessor of radiology of the University of Colorado Health Sciences Centerin Denver, will demonstrate the new, near-instantaneous transmission ofnuclear medicine images.andM;Nuclear medicine involves injecting radioactive isotopes into the body andtaking pictures on which the isotopes show physiological functions moreclearly than X-rays.andP;  With the new technique, a patient in one city can haveimages diagnosed in real-time by a doctor in another city.andM;Dr.andP;  Lear said the advances represented by combining technologies make itpossible to transmit images without compromising quality, using Macintosh IIpersonal computers.andP;  &quot;Normally you make images on X-ray film or use an$100-200,000 computer, which still delivers coarse images.andP;  We deliveredhardware and software to directly connect the Gamma cameras used to make thepictures into the Mac II, elminating the dedicated computers and film.andP;  Oncethe data is in the Mac II it's compatible with all standard networkingformats, and the VPN 56 is just a new network extension,&quot; Dr. Lear toldNewsbytes.andP;  Images and data are sent directly from a Gamma camera linked to aMacintosh II computer over the VPN 56 network.andM;This makes it possible to link outlying medical facilities to largerhealthcare centers so that physicians in different regions can consult withcomplete information on complex medical cases.andP;  &quot;Over the past year we'vedone clinical validation on this system for local image display.andP;  This is thefirst time we've tried to send the images nationally.andP;  We transmit in anon-compressed mode so you know the files aren't corrupted.&quot;andM;In addition to sending data, Dr. Lear is working on a technology to send TVpictures over phone lines, which would let doctors view patients as they viewdata.andP;  He's hoping to demonstrate that at the conference as well.andM;(Dana Blankenhorn/19900501/Press Contact: US Sprint, Paul Thibeau,816/276-6241)</TEXT></DOC>